2.  Size-structured linear dominance hierarchies were recognized among individuals inhabiting the same stream pools.  Observations on space utilization and foraging behaviour revealed fish to be either territorial or nonterritorial.  Within each local pool, dominant fish exclusively occupied the mid or surface layer of the pools as foraging territories, whereas subordinates adopted nonterritorial tactics, primarily utilizing the bottom layer.
